~ Prologue\: A Promise

[background arg="res://Assets/Noraneko_Backgrounds_Pack_2/Noraneko_Backgrounds_Pack_2/Livingroom_Dark.png" fade="2.0" wait="true"]

narrator: It was the kind of night that stays with you forever.
narrator: Heavy rain.
narrator: Cold wind pressing against the windows.
narrator: The kind of silence that only comes when something is about to end.

narrator: I was young then.
narrator: Old enough to understand loss.
narrator: Young enough to still believe promises could fix things.

narrator: I still remember every word.

[background arg="res://Assets/Noraneko_Background_Pack_1/Noraneko_Background_Pack_1/Futon_Room_Night.png" fade="1.0"]

narrator: The room smelled of medicine and old wood.
narrator: A single candle burned on the bedside table.
narrator: Her father lay beneath thin blankets, his breathing slow and shallow.

narrator: The village doctor had already done everything he could.
narrator: He had said nothing as he left.
narrator: That silence said enough.

Father: ...Thank you for coming.
Father: I know it's late.

player: Please don't talk too much.
player: You need to rest.

Father: Heh...
Father: Still worrying about everyone else before yourself.
Father: You've always been like that.
Father: Since you were small.

narrator: He smiled, but his eyes were tired.
narrator: The kind of tired that sleep couldn't fix.

narrator: His gaze slowly drifted toward the small girl sitting quietly beside the bed.
[background arg="res://Assets/1 (2).png" fade="2.5" wait="true"]

join bckup/Asami left [animation="Fade In" length="1.5" wait="true" extra_data="set CharacterOffset/Expressions/Sad1"]
[background arg="res://Assets/Noraneko_Background_Pack_1/Noraneko_Background_Pack_1/Futon_Room_Night.png" fade="2.5"]

narrator: She had been holding his hand since before I arrived.
narrator: She didn't cry.
narrator: She just held on.

narrator: She didn't fully understand what was happening.
narrator: Not completely.
narrator: But she understood enough to be afraid.

Father: Rin...
Father: Come closer.

Asami: ...Dad.

Father: It's alright.
Father: I'm not in pain.
Father: I just need you to listen carefully.
Father: Can you do that for me?

Asami: ...Yes.

Father: Good girl.

narrator: His hand trembled as he reached out to brush the hair from her face.
narrator: She leaned into his touch.

Father: There may come a day when I can't be beside you anymore.

Asami: Don't say that.
Asami: Don't say things like that.

Father: It's alright to be scared.
Father: I'm scared too.
Father: But some things can't be stopped.
Father: Only faced.

narrator: A long silence filled the room.
narrator: Only the rain spoke.

narrator: Then he turned back toward me.
narrator: His eyes were clear, even now.
narrator: Certain.

Father: After I'm gone...
Father: She'll be alone in this world.
Father: I don't want that for her.
Father: No parent would.

Father: Promise me you'll look after her.

player: ...

Father: Give her a home.
Father: Let her know she still belongs somewhere.
Father: Treat her not as a burden.
Father: But as family.

narrator: He paused, as if measuring his remaining strength.

Father: Make sure she smiles.
Father: Truly smiles.
Father: That's all I ask.
Father: That's everything I ask.

narrator: His hand reached slowly toward mine.
narrator: Cold.
narrator: Trembling.
narrator: But firm.

Father: Can you do that?

player: ...

narrator: The candle flickered.
narrator: Rin was watching me now.
narrator: Her small hands clutched the blanket.
narrator: Waiting.

player: I can.
player: I promise.

Father (expression="smile"): Good...
Father: That's enough for me.
Father: That's more than enough.

narrator: He closed his eyes.
narrator: His grip loosened, but didn't let go.

