narrator: Years passed.

narrator: Rin moved in with me.
narrator: She was quiet at first.
narrator: She would sit by the window for hours.
narrator: Watching the road.
narrator: As if some part of her still expected him to come back.
[background arg="res://Assets/rinveranda.png" fade="5.0" wait="true"]

narrator: Slowly, she found her footing.
narrator: She laughed again.
narrator: Small laughs at first.
narrator: Then real ones.

narrator: We grew older together.
narrator: Side by side.
narrator: Through ordinary days and unremarkable seasons.

narrator: And for a while, I believed the hardest part was over.
audio music "res://BGM/木陰の憩.mp3"

narrator: I was wrong.
[background arg="res://Assets/Noraneko_Background_Pack_1/Noraneko_Background_Pack_1/Sitting_Room_Dark.png" fade="3.0" wait="true"]

narrator: The sickness appeared without warning.

narrator: At first it was small.
narrator: Fatigue after light tasks.
narrator: A dizziness that came and went without reason.
narrator: Days where getting out of bed felt like climbing a mountain.

narrator: We thought it was exhaustion.
narrator: We thought rest would fix it.

narrator: Then weeks passed.
narrator: Then months.
narrator: Then years.

narrator: She never fully recovered between bad days.
narrator: The good days grew shorter.
narrator: The bad days grew longer.

narrator: Healers came.
narrator: They examined her carefully.
narrator: They left quietly.
narrator: None of them had answers.

narrator: No one could name what was wrong with her.
narrator: No medicine could slow it.
narrator: No treatment could stop it.

narrator: I watched her grow smaller.
narrator: Not in spirit.
narrator: In body.
narrator: In energy.
narrator: In the space she let herself take up in the world.

narrator: And I remembered the promise.
narrator: Make sure she smiles.

narrator: She still smiled.
narrator: Even now.
narrator: Even on the days she could barely sit up.
narrator: She smiled.

narrator: That made it worse.

narrator: I started searching for answers.
narrator: Old records in the village archive.
narrator: Traders passing through with knowledge of distant lands.
narrator: Rumors from adventurers who had gone deep into the dungeons below the eastern mountains.

narrator: And then I found it.
narrator: A single mention in a crumbling text.
narrator: Written in faded ink.
narrator: Barely legible.

narrator: The Elixir of Life.

narrator: A legendary medicine.
narrator: Said to cure any illness.
narrator: Said to restore what time and sickness had taken.
narrator: Said to exist somewhere deep within the dungeons.
narrator: Guarded by creatures and distance and danger.

narrator: Most dismissed it as myth.
narrator: A story told to give people hope where none existed.

narrator: But I had made a promise.

[background arg="black" fade="0.5"]

narrator: If the Elixir truly exists...
narrator: I will find it.

narrator: No matter how deep the dungeons go.
narrator: No matter how many times I have to come back empty-handed.
narrator: No matter how long it takes.

narrator: Because a promise isn't something you abandon.
narrator: Especially not when family is counting on you.
narrator: Especially not when she still smiles at you every morning.
narrator: Like you are the reason she bothered to wake up.

narrator: I won't let that smile disappear.
narrator: Not while I'm still breathing.

[background arg="res://Assets/Noraneko_Backgrounds_Pack_2/Noraneko_Backgrounds_Pack_2/Bedroom_Day.png" fade="2.0"]

narrator: Eight years later.
narrator: The same house.
narrator: A different morning.
narrator: The same promise.